<HEAD>Four Spies Penetrated Highest Levels Of British Intelligence</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Obit-Philby, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The following are biographical sketches of the four British traitors recruited at <ORGANIZATION> Cambridge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> in the 1930s by a Soviet agent who is still unidentified. _ <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Adrian </PERSON> <PERSON> Russell </PERSON> `` Kim'' <PERSON> Philby </PERSON> was regarded as the most damaging spy to Western intelligence. The only one of the <LOCATION> Cambridge </LOCATION> spy ring who was not a homosexual, he is believed to have become a Soviet agent in 1933, the year in which he saw fascists fighting communists and labor unionists in <LOCATION> Austria </LOCATION>. When entrusted with the Russian desk of MI6, the British intelligence unit that controls agents abroad, he told the Soviets who was spying on them. He served in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> as liaison officer with the <ORGANIZATION> CIA </ORGANIZATION>. He betrayed a British-U.S. plan to land guerrillas in communist <LOCATION> Albania </LOCATION> in 1946 and 300 were killed. He fled to <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> in 1963 while working as journalist in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>. _ <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Frederick </PERSON> <PERSON> Blunt </PERSON>, an art historian, recruited spies for <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> during the 1930s. He spied for the Soviets during World War II while working for the British MI5 counter-espionage service. He was unmasked in 1964 but was granted immunity in return for telling all he knew about Soviet intelligence. He was publicly exposed in 1979 and stripped of the knighthood conferred for his services as royal art adviser. He died in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> of a heart attack in 1983. _ <PERSON> Guy </PERSON> <PERSON> Francis </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Moncy </PERSON> <PERSON> Burgess </PERSON> became a Soviet agent in the 1930s because he believed only Soviet dictator <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Stalin </PERSON> could stop <PERSON> Adolf </PERS