rket will maintain its bullish trend, he said. Popular issues included shipbuildings and machineries. Chemicals, non-ferrous metals, textiles and rubbers also gained ground. Lower issues were steels and electricals. Volume of the first-section trade stood at an esimated 900 million shares, against 1.1 billion shares changed hands on Wednesday.
