Chinese civilians and captured soldiers killed by the Japanese in the <LOCATION> Nanking </LOCATION> massacre in the winter of 1937-38. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> signed a treaty in 1972 that says in part, `` The Japanese side is keenly aware of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s responsibility for causing enormous damages in the past to the <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> people through war and deeply reproaches itself.''
