<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Big Bird and scads of preschoolers are delighted and Oscar the grouch is predictably unimpressed. Perhaps the only ones nervous about Friday's `` wedding'' of <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> and <PERSON> Luis </PERSON> are the creators of `` Sesame Street.'' The marriage of two of the show's longtime characters represents the first attempt by the public television program, now in its 19th season, to show how romantic love works. <PERSON> Valeria </PERSON> <PERSON> Lovelace </PERSON>, the show's director of research, said the staff found `` no books for preschoolers on love and marriage, only death and divorce.'' When interviews with 90 <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> preschoolers showed that young children did not make the connection between love and marriage, the general outline of the theme was born. `` We wanted the wedding to make that connection for them,'' said Ms. <PERSON> Lovelace </PERSON>. The message has been carefully cultivated since last December, when <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> and <PERSON> Luis </PERSON>, longtime friends and partners in the show's Fix-It Shop, realized that their feelings were changing as they cared for a sick kitten together `` I saw them kiss,'' said <PERSON> Vicky </PERSON> <PERSON> Velasquez </PERSON>, a 4-year-old on a <LOCATION> Brooklyn </LOCATION> playground full of chatter about the impending match. `` So I know they're happy.'' `` We thought, ` What could we say to 3-year-olds about love?''' said <PERSON> Sonia </PERSON> <PERSON> Manzano </PERSON>, who plays <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> and writes for the show. `` And since kids see love in terms of physical things like kissing, hugging, giving flowers, we showed <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> and <PERSON> Luis </PERSON> doing a lot of that.'' <PERSON> Dulcy </PERSON> <PERSON> Singer </PERSON>, executive producer, said Ms. <PERSON> Manzano </PERSON>, who was married two years ago, inspired the wedding when she told her she was thinking about having a baby. The show was actually taped last January. Ms. <PERSON> Singer </PERSON> declined to say whether <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> and <PERSON> Luis </PERSON>, who is played by <PERSON> Emilio </PERSON> <PERSON> Delgado </PERSON>, would have a child after the wedding.
