<BYLINE>By EVANS WITT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Political Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said Thursday he `` could n't be more pleased'' with President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s endorsement of his Republican presidential bid, brushing aside as `` absolutely absurd'' suggestions that <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s support was unenthusiastic The <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> nominee-to-be refused to answer questions about a reported <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> deal with Panamanian strongman <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> that would involve dropping drug trafficking charges in exchange for his stepping down from power. `` I favor getting <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> out,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> told reporters at the <ORGANIZATION> Honeywell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Avionics </ORGANIZATION> plant in <LOCATION> Albuquerque </LOCATION>. `` I've learned something from some experience in this _ when negotiations are going on that are sensitive you do n't discuss them.'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> kicked off a seven-day western campaign swing with a slap at <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> front-runner <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>. `` We can not afford a radical swing. We can not afford a president who opposes every step we are taking to keep our defense at the technological edge,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> Albuquerque </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rotary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION> after the defense plant tour. He portrayed <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> as someone `` who opposes the MX, who opposes the Midgetman, who opposes testing of nuclear weapons ... who flirts with the withdrawal of our troops from <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>.'' <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> holds a primary on June 7 along with <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Monta