 Although <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> AB </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electrolux </ORGANIZATION> says it wants good relations with <ORGANIZATION> Murray </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ohio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manufacturing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> employees, the workers plan to tell the king and queen of <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION> they want no relations at all with <ORGANIZATION> Electrolux </ORGANIZATION>. <LOCATION> Murray </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>'s directors have rejected a $ 182 million, $ 48-a-share offer from <ORGANIZATION> Electrolux </ORGANIZATION>, a giant appliance manufacturer. <LOCATION> Murray </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, which makes lawn mowers and bicycles at <LOCATION> Lawrenceburg </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>, and is headquartered in <LOCATION> Brentwood </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>. On Wednesday, <ORGANIZATION> Murray </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ohio </ORGANIZATION> employees said they plan to send a petition to the king and queen of <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION> opposing the takeover The petition will be signed by 5,000 residents of <LOCATION> Lawrenceburg </LOCATION> and will accompany a letter to the president of <ORGANIZATION> Electrolux </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Anders </PERSON> <PERSON> Sharp </PERSON>, protesting the takeover effort, a spokesman said. The employees' news conference came a day after <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wiseman </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION> refused to lift a temporary restraining order suspending further action by <ORGANIZATION> Electrolux </ORGANIZATION> concerning <PERSON> Murray </PERSON>. Meanwhile, <PERSON> Scharp </PERSON> issued a statement which said, in part, `` <ORGANIZATION> Electrolux </ORGANIZATION> has no plans whatever to close the <LOCATION> Lawrenceburg </LOCATION> plant.'' <PERSON> Scharp </PERSON>