<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 252,195 cars and trucks this week, up from last week's 249,667, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday. Automakers produced 228,019 cars and trucks during the same week a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 166,915 cars this week, compared with 160,826 a week ago and 147,143 in the same week in 1987. Truck production for the week was scheduled at 85,280, compared with last week's 88,841 and last year's 80,876. Canadian automakers were to build 27,276 cars this week, compared with 26,727 last week and 16,239 in the same week last year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 20,305, compared with 20,634 last week and 16,828 in the same week last year.
