 on special savings accounts, called Super NOW accounts, also was unchanged at 5.13 percent. Bank Rate Monitor said the effective annual yield was 6.92 percent on six-month certificates of deposit, up from 6.86 percent the previous week. Yields were 7.23 percent on 1-year CDs, up from 7.19 percent; 7.65 percent on 2 -LCB- - year CDs, up from 7.61 percent; and 8.12 percent on 5-year CDs, up from 8.07 percent
